<item>
            <title>[LU-19491] add &quot;nodemap new&quot; alias for &quot;nodemap add&quot;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19491</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I think it is a bit confusing to have &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl nodemap add&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; create a new nodemap, and then &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nodemap add_range&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nodemap add_offset&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to modify the nodemap.  For OST Pools, the commands are &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl pool new&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl pool add&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, which gives a better distinction between the two operations IMHO.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it would be useful to add an alias &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nodemap new&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; that is equivalent to &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nodemap add&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and start documenting this as the preferred command (keeping &quot;&lt;tt&gt;nodemap add&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for compatibility.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="92979">LU-19491</key>
